data.value: The historic fortress, named after Himeji city of Japan, was built in 1346 to one of the dominant hills of the city. 46 meters high. Himeji Castle, which contains 83 building complexes, is known as the best example of Japanese castle architecture. At the beginning of the 1600s the castle was rebuilt and preserved for almost 400 years without any damage from World War II and natural disasters. Himeji Castle, which has been a UNESCO World Heritage Site since 1993, will be one of the most exciting addresses of your tour in Japan.
